# AWS Deployment Configuration
# 
# Copy this file to .env.deploy and fill in your actual values
# 
# To get these values:
# 1. S3_BUCKET_NAME: Your S3 bucket name (must be configured for static website hosting)
# 2. AWS_REGION: The AWS region where your S3 bucket is located (e.g., us-west-2, eu-west-1)
# 3. CLOUDFRONT_DISTRIBUTION_ID: Found in AWS Console > CloudFront > Distributions
# 4. CLOUDFRONT_URL: Your CloudFront distribution URL or custom domain
#
# Prerequisites:
# - AWS CLI installed and configured with appropriate permissions
# - S3 bucket with static website hosting enabled
# - CloudFront distribution pointing to your S3 bucket (optional but recommended)
#
# Usage: Run ./deploy.sh after setting up this configuration

S3_BUCKET_NAME=your-bucket-name
AWS_REGION=your-aws-region
CLOUDFRONT_DISTRIBUTION_ID=your-distribution-id
CLOUDFRONT_URL=https://your-domain.com